ons on image.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aFilms, cinema. 4aHistory of Science and Medicine. 4aMedia Studies. 4aMedia studies. 4aPsychiatry. 7aMEDICAL / Psychiatry / General.2bisacsh  aDeligny, cinema, image, radical psychiatry, French theory, media.1 aMiguel, Marlon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoses, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVogman, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978940060430840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789400604308423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789400604308/original  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK